where the modern Olympic Games were conceived 130 years ago.\", \"from\": 2850, \"to\": 3050, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2858, \"end\": 2863, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.191838029545037e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This will be the third time Paris has hosted the Olympics (1900 and 1924), tying London for the most as a Summer Games host.\", \"from\": 3051, \"to\": 3175, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3079, \"end\": 3084, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.191838029545037e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3132, \"end\": 3138, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.99999996286897, \"rank\": 2.4957823135616934e-08, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Los Angeles (1932, 1984) will tie those two cities when it hosts the first Summer Games in the U.S. in 32 years in 2028.\", \"from\": 3176, \"to\": 3296, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3176, \"end\": 3187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999521219263, \"rank\": 4.787000412663668e-08, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The organizers of Paris 2024 are reimagining the Games to make them more accessible to the public and to showcase their city to the world.\", \"from\": 3298, \"to\": 3436, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In a first, competitions will be held amidst iconic Parisian landmarks - beach 